issue.title: Extract user, group and role information from HTTP headers
issue.body:
This PR introduces a mechanism for extracting user, group and role information from HTTP headers and making it accessible through the following SQL functions:
 - `ontop_user()`
 - `ontop_contains_role_or_group('myRoleOrGroup')`

These functions can be used in SQL queries in the mapping and in lenses to implement access control.

It extracts information from the following HTTP headers: `x-user`, `x-roles` and `x-groups`.

By default, this information is not extracted. To enable, set `ontop.authorization=true`.

comment.body: Two more functions have been introduced in https://github.com/ontop/ontop/commit/528d41e6e5713386ef04ae33c4a81d1f0a0ee1c0 to distinguish roles from groups: `ontop_contains_role('myRole')` and `ontop_contains_group('myGroup')`

pull_request.title: Push b-node label anonymization into the IQTree
pull_request.body:
Currently b-node label anonymization and protection is ensured by:
   - Hashing at post-processing time the label string using a different salt generated for query
   - Treating the incoming blank nodes in SPARQL queries as variables so they cannot point to specific internal b-node labels
   - Not implementing the `str()` SPARQL function on b-nodes

This works fine for SPARQL query processing with post-processing. 
However, it does not work for other settings, like SPARQL query processing without post-processing.

This PR aims at bringing protections directly with IQ trees, with no special post-processing.
 - [x] Introduce the query-specific salt using the `QueryContext` object
 - [x] Split the bnode template function symbol into 2 function symbols: without and with the salt
 - [x] Evaluation with an equality constant should evaluate as false-or-null when the salt is not present
 - [x] Prevent simplification into a constant when the salt is not present
 - [x] Convert b-node constants into b-node templates
 - [x] Check TargetRendering (directly works with the template components)
 - [x] Check the SPARQL bnode function (builds a bnode template)

issue.title: No default schema in MS SQL Server for Ontop 5.1
issue.body: The JDBC driver for MS SQL Server in certain settings returns `null` instead of the default schema name. A special implementation of metadata extraction is provided to account for this case.
